Q2 — Multi-step (RAG + Tool): Cross-source reasoning
Query: "What does our contract say about missed deliveries, and how many has Acme Corp missed?"
================================================================================

Steps:
  [Tool Call] query_vendor_knowledge_base({'query': 'missed deliveries penalty clause'})
  [Tool Call] get_vendor_performance({'vendor_id': 'acme_corp'})

  [Tool Result] query_vendor_knowledge_base:
    [Source: acme_corp_contract.txt]
    3.3 Definition of Missed Delivery
    A "Missed Delivery" shall mean any instance in which:
      (i)  the applicable Deliverable is not received by Client on or before the
           Monthly Delivery Date;
      (ii) the Deliverable received materially fails to conform to the
           Specifications set forth in Exhibit B; or
      (iii) Vendor fails to provide the required pre-delivery notice as specified
            in Section 3.2.

    [Source: escalation_policy.txt]
    3. TIER 1 — FIRST MISSED DELIVERY: FORMAL WARNING
    3.1 Trigger
    Tier 1 is triggered immediately upon confirmation that a vendor has incurred
    one (1) Missed Delivery within any rolling 30-day period.

  [Tool Result] get_vendor_performance:
    Vendor: Acme Corp (acme_corp)
    Period: last 30 days
    Deliveries — Scheduled: 17 | On-time: 13 | Missed: 3 | Late: 1
    Uptime: 97.3%
    SLA breaches: 3
    Open incidents: 2
    Last incident: 2026-05-09 — payment processing service unresponsive for 83 minutes
    Compliance status:
      • ISO 27001: valid — expires 2026-08-23
      • Data Privacy Agreement: valid — expires 2026-10-11
      • Annual Security Audit: submitted 2026-02-19

Answer:
  Based on the contract terms, a "Missed Delivery" is defined as any instance
  where the Deliverable is not received by the Monthly Delivery Date, materially
  fails to conform to Specifications, or pre-delivery notice was not provided.

  According to our escalation policy, a Tier 1 Formal Warning is triggered
  immediately upon the first missed delivery within a rolling 30-day period.

  For Acme Corp over the last 30 days:
    Scheduled: 17 | On-time: 13 | Missed: 3 | Late: 1

  Acme Corp has missed 3 deliveries in the past month, which triggers a Tier 1
  escalation according to our policy.


